land","Carlton, Yorkshire, England":"Carlton, Yorkshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Sheffield","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name principally from Sheffield (Yorkshire), but perhaps also from Sheffield Bottom in Burghfield (Berkshire), or Sheffield Park in Fletching (Sussex). The Yorkshire place takes its name from the river Sheaf, itself from Old English <i>scēath</i> ‘boundary’, + Old English <i>feld</i> ‘open country’, while the Berkshire placename derives from Old English <i>scēo</i> ‘shelter’ + <i>feld</i>. The Sussex placename comes from Old English <i>scēap</i> ‘sheep’ + <i>feld</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Shuffield","meanings":["English: variant of   Sheffield  . This form of the surname is now rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":20,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":33,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":42,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Thomas Sheffield was born about 1295, in Wadsley, Yorkshire, England as the son of Robert de Sheffield III. He had at least 4 sons and 1 daughter with Agnes FitzAlan. He died in 1348, at the age of 54, and was buried in Bedale, North Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1295–1348":"umbes1295–1348","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1290–1348":"1290–1348","1326–1348":"1326–1348","1327–Male":"1327–Surnud","1328–1409":"1328–1409","1334–Female":"1334–Surnud","1334–Male":"1334–Surnud","1250–1312":"1250–1312","before 1348":"enne 1348","1295":"umbes 1295","1250":"1250","After 1312":"pärast 1312","After 1334":"pärast 1334","1290":"1290","1327":"1327","1326":"1326","1348":"1348","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1312":"1312","1334":"1334","1300":"1300","1453":"1453","1409":"1409","1328":"1328","after 1334":"pärast 1334","1317":"1317","Bedale, North Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bedale, North Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Wadsley, Yorkshire, England":"Wadsley, Yorkshire, England","Kirkstall, Yorkshire, England":"Kirkstall, Yorkshire, England","Carlton, Yorkshire, England":"Carlton, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1295–1348":"noin1295–1348","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1290–1348":"1290–1348","1326–1348":"1326–1348","1327–Male":"1327–Kuollut","1328–1409":"1328–1409","1334–Female":"1334–Kuollut","1334–Male":"1334–Kuollut","1250–1312":"1250–1312","before 1348":"ennen vuotta 1348","1295":"noin 1295","1250":"1250","After 1312":"1312 jälkeen","After 1334":"1334 jälkeen","1290":"1290","1327":"1327","1326":"1326","1348":"1348","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1312":"131